    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about needing an escrow account for this house i'm looking at in toronto. i've never bought a place before so i'm kinda lost. can u explain what escrow actually is and why it's even used in the closing process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in a nutshell, is a temporary holding account, usually managed by a neutral third party, like a lawyer or a title company. Think of it as a secure, temporary stash for the money and documents involved in the house sale. It's used to make sure that both the buyer and the seller fulfill their obligations before the transaction is finalized, preventing anyone from getting burned. This keeps the whole closing process safe and orderly, which is crucial when dealing with such a big investment.",
