      "content": "The management of the escrow account is handled by the designated escrow agent—that neutral third party we mentioned earlier. They are legally responsible for the funds and documents, operating under strict rules and regulations. They act as the gatekeeper, ensuring that the money only moves from the buyer to the seller (or to cover agreed-upon costs) *after* all the conditions of the sale have been met. This oversight is what keeps the process trustworthy.",
